survey_response.review_text: Dr. Reddy is a godsend to us. My father is a Chronic Kidney Disease Patient and was diagnosed with Military Tuberculosis on November 2019 and he was on ATT since then. He was admitted in ICU with serious health conditions and was unconscious for 4 days at a stretch. He wasn’t able to breathe on his own and was on Oxygen supply but today touchwood he is fine. He was bedridden post his admission in the ICU.  There was a point when we lost hope, but Dr.Reddy didn’t give up on my father.He goes out of his way to make sure all your questions are answered and he works with you to address the health concerns rather than just telling you what needs to be done. And also he cares for his patients a lot and follows up for regular update. He is very approachable and walked us through every minute details. Today after almost 1.5 years my father has been able to walk around, can breathe easy and there is no sign of TB. When I see my father today its almost unbelievable that he is the same man who was admitted in ICU and was struggling for his life. It feels like a miracle. We as a family can’t thank Dr. Reddy enough for his relentless support, guidance and encouragement during this entire journey.

survey_response.review_text: I have asthma from childhood but did not face any severe issues. Mild symptoms used to be easily subdued by general medication. I had a PFT test during the annual health check up to find the lung capacity was below normal and medication was prescribed. I wanted to visit a specialist before taking any long term medication. This is when I visited Dr Gangireddy TK. He explained it very well that there is nothing to worry about such PFT results and it is quite expected for people with mild asthma. Instead of stronger oral medication he suggested me milder inhale medication. I could feel remarkable improvement in my breathing and feel a greater lung capacity after undergoing treatment from him. He is a next gen doctor who will explain the issue in detail and would also encourage you to google more about it to have better understanding (not take medication from Google of course!) and suggest small lifestyle changes that will help and to avoid allergents rather than undergoing medication. I would strongly recommend him for respiratory and allergic issues.

He is also very polite and generous and gives sufficient time to explain the plan of treatment to his patient. I highly recommend Dr Gangi Reddy.
